  "text": "In a multithreaded environment, different executions of an algorithm are likely to process vertices in different orderings, which could change the runtime of an algorithm. To measure the sensitivity of matching algorithms to the multithreaded environment, we run each algorithm 20 times for each input graph and compute the variation in parallel runtimes. Following prior notation [CITATION_1] , we measure the parallel sensitivity (c) of an algorithm as the ratio of the standard deviation (s) of runtimes from 20 runs, to the mean of runtimes (m): c ¼ s m Â 100. For all input graphs of Table 3 , we computed c for MS-BFS-Graft, PF, and PR algorithms using 40 threads on Mirasol. On average, the variation in runtimes is higher for PF (17 percent) and PR (10 percent) relative to the MS-BFS-Graft algorithm (6 percent).",
